data.chText: （尤指因气愤或害怕，使浑身或身体的一部分）变僵硬，变僵直，绷紧
data.enText: to make yourself or part of your body firm, straight and still, especially because you are angry or frightened

data.chText: 我挺直了腰杆面对着他。
data.enText: I stiffened my back and faced him.
to become, or to make sth become, difficult to bend or move

data.chText: 爬上去以后我两腿都发僵了。
data.enText: My muscles had stiffened up after the climb.
to make an attitude or idea stronger or more powerful; to become stronger

data.chText: 惩罚的威胁益发坚定了他们的决心。
data.enText: The threat of punishment has only stiffened their resolve (= made them even more determined to do sth) .
to make sth, such as cloth, firm and unable to bend

word_means: 难以弯曲，难以活动，发僵

means: (尤指因气愤或害怕，使浑身或身体的一部分)变僵硬，变僵直，绷紧

trans: （肌肉或关节）变得僵硬；（使）变得不易弯曲；（使）变得不灵活

example: Stiffen the cream by adding gelatine
He stiffened when he saw his boss enter the room

value.def: If you stiffen, you stop moving and stand or sit with muscles that are suddenly tense, for example because you feel afraid or angry.

example.ex: Ada stiffened at the sound of his voice...
example.tran: 埃达听到他的声音吓得人都僵住了。

example.ex: The father's face stiffened with dismay.
example.tran: 父亲因为悲痛而面部表情凝重。

value.tran: 变得僵硬;变得紧张;绷紧

value.def: If your muscles or joints stiffen, or if something stiffens them, they become difficult to bend or move.

example.ex: The blood supply to the skin is reduced when muscles stiffen.
example.tran: 当肌肉变得僵硬时，皮肤的供血量就减少了。

example.ex: These clothes restrict your freedom of movement and stiffen up the whole body...
example.tran: 这些衣服使你行动不便，让全身都变得不灵活。

example.ex: 'I just stiffened up, and the more they told me to 'be natural', the more I felt not at all relaxed.'
example.tran: “我整个人都僵硬了，他们越是让我‘自然些’，我就越紧张。”

value.tran: (肌肉或关节)变得僵硬;(使)变得不易弯曲;(使)变得不灵活

value.def: If attitudes or behaviour stiffen, or if something stiffens them, they become stronger or more severe, and less likely to be changed.

example.ex: Russian resistance suddenly stiffened because there was no room for retreat...
example.tran: 俄罗斯的反抗突然变得强硬起来，因为已经没有退路了。

example.ex: Canada has recently stiffened its immigration rules.
example.tran: 加拿大最近制定了更为严格的移民规定。

value.tran: (态度或行为)变得更强硬，变得更严厉;(使)变得更坚定

value.def: If something such as cloth is stiffened, it is made firm so that it does not bend easily.

example.ex: This special paper was actually thin, soft Sugiwara paper that had been stiffened with a kind of paste...
example.tran: 这种特殊的纸实际是一种糨糊浆过的又薄又软的杉原纸。

example.ex: They peeled cold stiffened gloves from their hands.
example.tran: 他们将冻得硬邦邦的手套从手上脱下来。
